snippet: Venus Williams, who was unseeded, won the Wuhan Open in China on Saturday when fifth-seeded Garbiñe Muguruza retired with a left ankle injury while trailing, 6-3, 3-0.
abstract: Venus Williams beats Garbine Muguruza to win Wuhan Open for her 47th WTA singles title; other tennis results noted.
lead_paragraph: Venus Williams, who was unseeded, won the Wuhan Open in China on Saturday when fifth-seeded Garbiñe Muguruza retired with a left ankle injury while trailing, 6-3, 3-0.
